+#!/usr/bin/env bash
+# Open a PR for campaign-3.0/ against RobertLee8888/campaign main.
+#
+# Just run it — no arguments needed. It auto-detects your local
+# campaign repo clone:
+#
+#   bash ~/Documents/Claude/Projects/Alva-design/campaign-3.0/open-pr.sh
+#
+# Override the clone path with $REPO if needed:
+#
+#   REPO=~/wherever/campaign \
+#     bash ~/Documents/Claude/Projects/Alva-design/campaign-3.0/open-pr.sh
+
+set -euo pipefail
+
+SRC="$HOME/Documents/Claude/Projects/Alva-design/campaign-3.0"
+BRANCH="feat/campaign-3.0"
+BASE="main"
+
+# 1. Locate the local campaign clone.
+CANDIDATES=(
+  "${REPO:-}"
+  "$PWD"
+  "$HOME/code/campaign"
+  "$HOME/Code/campaign"
+  "$HOME/projects/campaign"
+  "$HOME/Projects/campaign"
+  "$HOME/Documents/code/campaign"
+  "$HOME/Documents/Projects/campaign"
+  "$HOME/Documents/GitHub/campaign"
+  "$HOME/github/campaign"
+  "$HOME/src/campaign"
+  "$HOME/work/campaign"
+)
+REPO_PATH=""
+for d in "${CANDIDATES[@]}"; do
+  [ -z "$d" ] && continue
+  if [ -d "$d/.git" ]; then
+    url=$(git -C "$d" config --get remote.origin.url 2>/dev/null || echo "")
+    if echo "$url" | grep -qi "RobertLee8888/campaign"; then
+      REPO_PATH="$d"
+      break
+    fi
+  fi
+done
+
+# Fallback: search the home tree (skip hidden dirs + node_modules).
+if [ -z "$REPO_PATH" ]; then
+  echo "→ scanning \$HOME for RobertLee8888/campaign clone (may take a sec)…"
+  while IFS= read -r d; do
+    url=$(git -C "$(dirname "$d")" config --get remote.origin.url 2>/dev/null || echo "")
+    if echo "$url" | grep -qi "RobertLee8888/campaign"; then
+      REPO_PATH="$(dirname "$d")"
+      break
+    fi
+  done < <(find "$HOME" -name ".git" -type d \
+              -not -path "*/node_modules/*" \
+              -not -path "*/Library/*" \
+              -not -path "*/.Trash/*" 2>/dev/null)
+fi
+
+if [ -z "$REPO_PATH" ]; then
+  cat <<EOF >&2
+✖ couldn't find your local RobertLee8888/campaign clone.
+
+If you haven't cloned it yet:
+  git clone https://github.com/RobertLee8888/campaign.git ~/code/campaign
+  REPO=~/code/campaign bash $0
+
+If you have, re-run with the path:
+  REPO=/path/to/your/campaign bash $0
+EOF
+  exit 1
+fi
+
+echo "✓ found local repo: $REPO_PATH"
+cd "$REPO_PATH"
+
+if [ ! -d "$SRC" ]; then
+  echo "✖ source missing: $SRC" >&2
+  exit 1
+fi
+
+echo "→ syncing latest from origin/$BASE"
+git fetch origin "$BASE"
+
+echo "→ creating $BRANCH off origin/$BASE"
+if git show-ref --verify --quiet "refs/heads/$BRANCH"; then
+  git checkout "$BRANCH"
+  git reset --hard "origin/$BASE"
+else
+  git checkout -b "$BRANCH" "origin/$BASE"
+fi
+
+echo "→ copying campaign-3.0/ from Alva-design"
+mkdir -p ./campaign-3.0
+rsync -a --delete --exclude='open-pr.sh' "$SRC/" ./campaign-3.0/
+
+echo "→ staging + committing"
+git add campaign-3.0
+if git diff --cached --quiet; then
+  echo "✖ no staged changes — campaign-3.0 already matches base" >&2
+  exit 1
+fi
+git commit -m "feat(campaign-3.0): FinTwit Alpha League rebuild (rounds 1–46, lens shader + mobile + card chrome)
+
+Page structure (top → bottom):
+- Hero (Section 1) → 'You follow @___ on X' typewriter handle cycle
+  (8 creators) with a 18-card animated tweet drift behind the headline.
+  Rendered through a Three.js + WebGL post-processing pass: per-tier
+  depth-of-field blur, Brown's k1 barrel distortion gated to the
+  outer ring, industry-standard radial chromatic aberration (3 barrel
+  samples / channel composited onto bg before R/G/B pick — no boundary
+  hack), film grain, and an aspect-corrected radial edge color shift
+  toward neutral grey ('白心淡灰晕'). Distortion strength softened +
+  smoothstep widened so center cards stay clean and the transition to
+  edge curvature is gradual, not a hard cut. Each tweet bitmap is
+  pre-rendered to canvas with a 1px light-grey stroke for definition.
+- Coverage / Backtested (Section 2) → 2-row card marquee + headline
+  overlay. Headline left-aligned with a 3-layer progressive backdrop
+  blur (15/30/60px) masked through a 1250px window so the type sits
+  over a heavy-glass plaque without bleeding to the section edges.
+  Plaque color matched to the bg composite (#f0f7f8) so it dissolves
+  into the mint wash instead of reading as a white sticker. Left fade
+  zone widened. Buttons: solid black primary pill + black-bordered
+  ghost pill. Card shadows + borders re-hued from neutral grey to
+  alva mint so they don't read dirty on the green wash.
+- Alpha League (Section 3) → centered head + full-width table.
+  padding-top 96 + h2 clamp(28, 3.4vw, 46) — matched exactly to S4's
+  scale so the two non-hero headings read as one typographic tier.
+  Table window capped at 540px with a fade mask so it implies 'scroll
+  for the full board'. A multi-hue conic backdrop sits BEHIND the
+  lb-card with hue-rotate animation (visibly cycles colors), masked
+  with a vertical alpha gradient so the visible peek is wide at the
+  bottom of the card and invisible at the top (trapezoid feel via
+  soft mask, NOT a polygon — earlier clip-path attempt was retired).
+- Playbooks (Section 4) → 'Each creator's playbook, distilled into
+  an AI agent.' Wide landscape cards in a snap-rail carousel. Tab
+  divider recolored to mint so it actually reads on the bg. Card
+  spacing rebuilt: cover→title 24px (far), title→body 4px (near),
+  body→CTA 16px — title + body now read as a paired block, more
+  separated from the cover above them.
+- Backtest (Section 5) → 'Backtest one creator, or scan every
+  creator you follow.' Two cards: inline @handle form + Connect X
+  CTA that opens #modal-connect. Submit flips card to a queued state
+  in place.
+
+Nav:
+- 4 scrollspy tabs (Coverage / Alpha League / Playbooks) with the
+  Backtest section anchored too. Flat text + thin alva underline
+  indicator. Section anchors land flush below nav (65px offset).
+
+Layout / cadence + bg system:
+- Section bg cadence: white(S1) → mint-wash(S2) → white(S3) →
+  mint-wash(S4) → footer matches S4. Adjacent sections always
+  alternate. The mint wash is a 2-blob radial recipe on top of an
+  8% alva base, identical formula in S2 and S4 so they read as
+  paired siblings.
+- Background animations on S2 / S4 were prototyped (mesh blobs,
+  conic gradients, dot grids, noise, grid lines, particle network,
+  sine waves, ribbon curves, vector flow fields) and removed —
+  every variant either duplicated the leaderboard halo's color-
+  shift vocabulary or read as a dev-tutorial cliché. Sections now
+  rely on the static mint wash for a clean baseline.
+
+Mobile parity (round 44):
+- Phone media block restructured by section (nav / S1 / S2 / S3
+  / S4 / footer / modals) with comments. Legacy 2.0 rules kept as
+  no-ops in case markup ever reverts.
+- S1 → softer H1 + sub typography (clamp 28-38 / 15-19), six-layer
+  white halo retuned for the narrower viewport so the H1 stays
+  legible over the drifting tweet cards, tweet density dropped to
+  4 (was 6) with smaller tier widths. Three.js WebGL lens pass
+  skipped on ≤760 — the barrel-distortion radius collapses into
+  the headline column at that width so the visual payoff
+  disappears; DOM tweets stay visible and battery stays cheap.
+- S2 → desktop's 1250px backdrop-blur mask covered the whole phone
+  viewport and dimmed the marquee to invisibility; on mobile the
+  overlay is reverted to normal flow (block, no inset, no mask,
+  no backdrop-filter), the headline sits above the marquee with
+  18px gutters, mq-cards drop to 196×178. .stage.stage-marquee
+  also reset from display:flex to block so the title doesn't ride
+  beside the marquee as a row.
+- S3 → leaderboard table grid was the critical clip: desktop's
+  7-col template needs 350+ px but the phone content area is only
+  306. Header now matches row (4 cols: 22 / 1fr / 58 / 52 with 8px
+  gap, 12px padding). .who's unnamed wrapper div gets
+  min-width:0 / flex:1 / overflow:hidden so the b + span actually
+  ellipsize instead of bleeding into the ROI cell. ROI / Risk
+  pills now render in full at 360-class widths.
+- S4 → tab strip horizontally scrollable, cards flex 0 0
+  calc(100vw - 56px) max 340, h3/p/CTA scaled down a notch,
+  carousel padding 18px so the next card peek hints 'more →'.
+- Modals → tighter padding, full-width primary + ghost CTAs.
+- 380px sub-breakpoint pulls table columns + section padding
+  tighter still for iPhone SE-class phones.
+
+Terminology + UX:
+- Global KOL → FinTwit creator / FinTwit account. Brand word
+  'FinTwit Alpha League' for the leaderboard.
+- Nav CTAs: 'For FinTwit creators' opens modal directly. 'Test any
+  FinTwit creator' opens connect modal.
+
+Engineering:
+- Marquee uses Web Animations API for jitter-free pause/resume.
+- GPU-composited mq-card hover, paint containment isolates
+  leaderboard repaint. lb-meta dot pulse removed.
+- WebGL canvas pre-rasterizes tweet bitmaps; per-tier blur applied
+  on the bitmap (not via GPU shader) for crisp DoF tiers.
+- do-test-form submit handler normalizes @handle + flips card
+  in place without leaving the page.
+
+Floating-card chrome (rounds 45 → 46.14, post mobile parity):
+- Iterated the floating-tweet card visuals after the user kept
+  flagging a thin grey ring at every card edge — which I initially
+  misdiagnosed as a stroke / shadow problem (rounds 45 → 45.3
+  cycled through removing border, removing shadow, then both),
+  then as a shader composite issue (round 46 swapped mix() for
+  premultiplied 'over' which removed the ring but killed the CA at
+  section edges, round 46.3 reverted), then as a sRGB color-space
+  conversion artifact (round 46.9 switched to NoColorSpace), then
+  as a canvas2D filter:blur side effect (round 46.11 zeroed
+  per-tier blur).
+- REAL ROOT CAUSE (round 46.12 / 46.13): GPU bilinear sampler was
+  interpolating between card-edge texels (1,1,1, X) and the
+  transparent-black shadowPad pad area (0,0,0, 0), producing grey
+  RGB exactly at the card boundary. The grey was inherent to the
+  sampler, not anything the canvas or shader was doing. Two-step
+  fix: (a) put the shadow back (now safe to do — canvas drop-shadow
+  rgba(20,20,30, 0.06), blur 44, offsetY 4) so the shadowPad pad
+  is filled with the shadow's halo color instead of (0,0,0, 0);
+  (b) set material.premultipliedAlpha=true so the scene→RT blend
+  uses gl.ONE, preserving straight-alpha values into the RT.
+- Round 46.14 — restored a deliberate hairline: 5% black stroke
+  (canvas: rgba(0,0,0, 0.05) lineWidth 1; matching CSS: 1px solid
+  rgba(0,0,0, 0.05) for the mobile DOM fallback). Now a real
+  designed line, not the phantom sampler line from before.
+- Round 46.15 — translucent stroke compounded with bilinear edge
+  artifact; switched to SOLID #e5e5ea (--line token) so the
+  border overwrites the underlying sample value cleanly.
+- Round 46.16 — canvas2D stroke() anti-aliasing still produced
+  visible per-side variation; replaced with two-fill technique
+  (outer #e5e5ea rect slightly bigger, white card on top). The
+  visible 1px band is pure #e5e5ea pixels with no AA touching
+  them.
+- Rounds 46.17 → 46.21 — chased a remaining 'dark line outside
+  the border' through shadow offset adjustment, plane integer
+  snapping, shadow blur tightening, and aligning the shadow RGB
+  with the border (#e5e5ea). Pixel probe at each step.
+- Round 46.22 — DIAGNOSTIC dropping canvas shadow entirely
+  confirmed the dark line was a canvas2D shadow rendering quirk
+  through the WebGL pipeline, not an alpha-mismatch / composite
+  issue. Probe values went uniform (253-255) on all 4 sides as
+  soon as the shadow stopped being drawn.
+- Round 46.23 — going to radius=0 (square corners) eliminated the
+  per-corner AA artifact (a 1px border on a 45° arc spreads over
+  1.4 pixels, less coverage per pixel, visibly darker than the
+  straight edges). User feedback: too brutalist.
+- Round 46.24 — landing on radius=5/6 as a compromise: only ~8
+  device pixels of arc per corner so the AA mismatch falls under
+  the visual detection threshold while the cards regain a soft
+  tile feel.
+- Final state: 1 logical px solid #e5e5ea border via the two-fill
+  technique, radius 5/6 corners, no canvas shadow, plane positions
+  snapped to integer device pixels. CSS DOM fallback uses
+  1px solid #e5e5ea border.
+- CA strength (uCA) tuned 0.005 → 0.020 (4×) so the edge
+  chromatic aberration is clearly readable across card boundaries
+  and headline text strokes.
+- Film grain mask (round 46.18) — radial smoothstep(0.15, 1.0, r²)
+  applied to uGrain so the H1 column stays clean and only the
+  section corners pick up the old-TV noise.
+
+Three.js load timing (round 46.4):
+- A parallel optimization moved Three.js to a deferred dynamic
+  <script>; the inline lens IIFE was bailing out via
+  'if (typeof THREE === undefined) return' before the deferred
+  script finished loading, so the lens never initialized.
+  Replaced the hard bail with a polling waitForThree(initLens)
+  with a 10s ceiling."
+
+echo "→ pushing $BRANCH"
+git push -u origin "$BRANCH"
+
+if command -v gh >/dev/null 2>&1; then
+  echo "→ opening PR via gh"
+  gh pr create --base "$BASE" --head "$BRANCH" \
+    --title "Campaign 3.0 — FinTwit Alpha League rebuild" \
+    --body "Cumulative output of feedback rounds 1 → 46 (Slack #proj-kolplaybook + same-day iterations). See campaign-3.0/README.md for narrative spine.
+
+**Hero (S1)** — Three.js + WebGL post-pass over a canvas of 18 floating tweets. Industry-standard radial chromatic aberration (3 barrel samples / channel composited onto bg before R/G/B pick), Brown's k1 barrel distortion gated to the outer ring with a wide smoothstep ramp (no hard edge cut), per-tier DoF blur, film grain, neutral-grey CRT vignette. Card bitmaps carry a 1px light-grey stroke for definition.
+
+**Coverage (S2)** — Headline overlay uses a 3-layer progressive backdrop-filter blur (15/30/60px) masked through a 1250px window. Plaque color matches the bg composite (#f0f7f8) so it dissolves into the mint wash. Left fade zone widened. Solid black primary button + black-bordered ghost button. Card shadows + borders re-hued to alva mint.
+
+**Alpha League (S3)** — padding-top 96 + title clamp(28, 3.4vw, 46) — paired exactly with S4's scale. Table capped at 540px with a fade mask. Behind the lb-card: a multi-hue conic backdrop with hue-rotate animation, masked with a vertical alpha gradient so the visible peek is wide at the bottom of the card and invisible at the top (trapezoid feel via soft mask).
+
+**Playbooks (S4)** — Tab divider recolored to mint. Card spacing rebuilt: cover→title 24px (far), title→body 4px (near), body→CTA 16px.
+
+**Backtest (S5)** — inline @handle form + Connect X CTA.
+
+**Cadence** — white → mint-wash → white → mint-wash → footer follows last. Identical mint-wash formula in S2/S4 so they read as paired siblings.
+
+**Background animations on S2/S4** — prototyped 9 variants (mesh blobs, conic, dot grid, noise, grid lines, particle network, sine waves, ribbon curves, vector flow field) — all removed. Section bgs now rely on the static mint wash for a clean baseline.
+
+**Mobile parity (round 44)** — phone media block restructured by section. Critical fixes: (a) S3 leaderboard table grid was clipping the ROI + Risk columns at ≤390px because the desktop 7-col template overflowed the 306px content area; new 4-col 22/1fr/58/52 template + min-width:0 on .who's wrapper div so b/span actually ellipsize. (b) S2's 1250px backdrop-blur mask covered the entire phone viewport and dimmed the marquee to invisibility; on mobile the overlay reverts to normal flow with no mask + no backdrop-filter, and .stage.stage-marquee resets from flex to block so the headline doesn't ride beside the marquee. (c) S1 H1 halo retuned (six layers, narrower radii), tweet density dropped to 4; WebGL lens pass skipped at ≤760 to save battery — the lens' barrel-distortion radius collapses into the headline column at phone widths. (d) S4 carousel cards reflow to calc(100vw - 56px). (e) New 380px sub-breakpoint for iPhone SE-class phones. Verified at 390 / 375 / 360 / 768 via Playwright screenshots.
+
+**Floating card chrome (rounds 45 → 46.24)** — extended debugging chain on the floating-tweet card visuals in S1. The user kept reporting a thin grey ring / dark line at card edges; I cycled through many wrong hypotheses (stroke alpha, shadow shape, sRGB color space, canvas blur, alpha premultiplication, two different shader composites, etc) before pinning it. The actual roots, in order of discovery: (1) GPU bilinear interpolation between border texels (1,1,1) and transparent-black shadowPad pixels (0,0,0,0) produced grey at the boundary; fixed by filling that pad with the shadow halo and setting material.premultipliedAlpha=true. (2) canvas2D stroke() anti-aliases against surrounding pixels, giving uneven side-to-side contrast; replaced with a two-fill technique (outer #e5e5ea rect slightly larger than the white inner rect, no stroke involved). (3) canvas2D shadow rendering through the WebGL pipeline produces an asymmetric darkness on the long card axis that no parameter tuning resolved — confirmed by a diagnostic round that dropped the shadow entirely and saw the uneven probe values go uniform; the shadow stays out in the final state. (4) Rounded corners with 1px borders show a corner AA artifact (the 1px band spreads over 1.4 pixels diagonally); landed on radius 5/6 as the smallest visible rounding without the artifact reaching perceptual threshold. Final state: 1 logical px solid #e5e5ea border via two-fill technique, radius 5/6 corners, plane positions snapped to integer device pixels, no canvas shadow.
+
+**CA strength + grain mask** — uCA bumped 0.005 → 0.020 (4×) so the edge chromatic aberration is clearly visible on card boundaries and headline text. Film grain gets a radial mask (smoothstep(0.15, 1.0, r²)) so the H1 column stays clean and only the section corners pick up the old-TV noise.
+
+**Three.js load race (round 46.4)** — a parallel optimization moved Three.js to a deferred dynamic script tag; the inline lens IIFE was bailing out before THREE finished loading, so the lens never initialized. Replaced the hard 'if (typeof THREE === undefined) return' bail with a polling waitForThree(initLens) waiter.
+
+**Preview after merge**
+https://robertlee8888.github.io/campaign/campaign-3.0/
+
+**Outstanding (separate PRs)**
+- Real /scan/* flow (currently demo lightbox)
+- /request page"
+else
